Former Congressman Ike Skelton, who served the people of Missouri for 34 years in the United States Congress, has passed away. He was highly regarded by his colleagues and was known for his dedication to the military as the Chairman of the Armed Services Committee. Skelton was seen as a mentor and friend to many in Congress and across Missouri, and he will be missed. President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama extend their condolences to Skelton's wife, Patty, his family, and loved ones.